claims:
1. A method of maintaining machine learning model data privacy comprising:
training a machine learning model forming part of a data science process using data anonymized using each of two or more differential privacy mechanisms;
determining, for each of the two or more differential privacy mechanisms, a level of accuracy and a level precision when evaluating data with known classifications;
determining, using the respective determined levels of precision and accuracy, a mitigation efficiency ratio for each of the two or more differential privacy mechanisms; and
incorporating the differential privacy mechanism having a highest mitigation efficiency ratio and its parameters into the data science process.

10. A computer program product comprising non-tangible storage media storing instructions, which when executed by at least one computing device, implement operations for maintaining machine learning model data privacy comprising:
training a machine learning model forming part of a data science process using data anonymized using each of two or more differential privacy mechanisms;
determining, for each of the two or more differential privacy mechanisms, a level of accuracy and a level precision when evaluating data with known classifications;
determining, using the respective determined levels of precision and accuracy, a mitigation efficiency ratio for each of the two or more differential privacy mechanisms; and
automatically incorporating the differential privacy mechanism having a highest mitigation efficiency ratio and its parameters into the data science process without human intervention.

11. The computer program product of claim 10, wherein:
a first of the two or more differential privacy mechanisms comprises local differential privacy (LDP);
the LDP is realized using local randomizers;
the LDP anonymizes the training data prior to its being used to train the machine learning model;
a second of the two or more differential privacy mechanisms comprises differential privacy stochastic descent gradient (DP-SGD);
the DP-SGD anonymizes the training data while it is being used to train the machine learning model.
